            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>2989</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.3.3</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.3.3.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:number>8.3.3</fr:number>
                <fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-8.3</fr:parent>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Consider a diagram of the form <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.1.1" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.1.1.xml" taxon="Equation" number="8.3.1.1" /> as in (ii) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.2" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.2.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="8.3.2" />.
    By (V) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5" href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5.xml" number="5.3.5" />, the map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^\bullet {(X_\bullet ,\mathbb {Z})\to \operatorname {H}^\bullet (Z_\bullet ,\mathbb {Z})}]]></fr:tex> is an isomorphism.
    In <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.19" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.19.xml" number="8.1.19" /> and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.20" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.20.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="8.1.20" />, we endowed <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^\bullet (Z_\bullet ,\mathbb {Z})]]></fr:tex> with a mixed Hodge structure, and obtained a mixed Hodge structure on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^\bullet (X_\bullet ,\mathbb {Z})]]></fr:tex>.
    
    This is independent of the choice of diagram of the form <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.1.1" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.1.1.xml" taxon="Equation" number="8.3.1.1" />: by (ii) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.2" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.2.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="8.3.2" /> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f=\mathrm {Id}]]></fr:tex>. any two systems <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[({Z_\bullet }_i,{\overline {Z}_\bullet }_i,p_i)_{i=1,2}]]></fr:tex> are always covered by a third <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(Z_\bullet ,\overline {Z}_\bullet ,p)]]></fr:tex>, whence a commutative diagram of isomorphisms

    
  <fr:embedded-tex hash="d4632a0f985d07c9e3b6a7c7500bdc0c"><fr:embedded-tex-preamble><![CDATA[
    \usepackage {amsmath}
    \usepackage {amssymb}
    \usepackage {tikz-cd}
  ]]></fr:embedded-tex-preamble><fr:embedded-tex-body><![CDATA[\begin {tikzcd}
      & \operatorname {H}^\bullet (X_\bullet ,\mathbb {Z})
        \ar [dl] \ar [d] \ar [dr]
    \\\operatorname {H}^\bullet ({Z_\bullet }_1,\mathbb {Z})
        \ar [r]
      & \operatorname {H}^\bullet (Z_\bullet ,\mathbb {Z})
      & \operatorname {H}^\bullet ({Z_\bullet }_2,\mathbb {Z})
        \ar [l]
    \end {tikzcd}]]></fr:embedded-tex-body></fr:embedded-tex></fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>2990</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.3.4</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.3.4.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:number>8.3.4</fr:number>
                <fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-8.3</fr:parent>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>The <fr:em>mixed Hodge structure</fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^\bullet (X_\bullet ,\mathbb {Z})]]></fr:tex> is the one defined above.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>It follows from (ii) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.2" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.3.2.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="8.3.2" /> that this mixed Hodge structure is functorial in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X_\bullet ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>2991</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.3.5</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.3.5.xml</fr:route>
